From the lords of the soil, in their several degrees, and from the lords of the soil only, could the material aid that was needed be expected ; and, as we have noticed‚ their aid came in slowly, and, as it were, reluctantly. If we scruti- nise the catalogue of grants tabulated in No. CCCLXIX. Moreover, in this same connection, another considera- tion is that the F oundation grant—nay, that the ulti- mate whole of Espec's grant—is not of an overwhelming nature.
